hands_on_practices.problem:
A charged pion of mass $m_{\pi}$ moves with a constant rapidity $\phi_{\pi}$ along the positive x-axis of a laboratory frame. The pion subsequently decays into a muon of mass $m_{\mu}$ and a muon neutrino of mass $m_{
u}$. In the pion's rest frame, the decay products are emitted along the axis of the pion's motion, with the muon traveling in the direction of the pion's original velocity and the neutrino in the opposite direction. Determine the rapidities of the muon, $\phi_{\mu}$, and the neutrino, $\phi_{
u}$, in the laboratory frame. Express your answer as an ordered pair of symbolic expressions $(\phi_{\mu}, \phi_{
u})$ in terms of $m_{\pi}$, $m_{\mu}$, $m_{
u}$, and $\phi_{\pi}$.
